As see in the documentation [here|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Configuring+User+Directories#ConfiguringUserDirectories-UpdatingDirectories] JIRA behaves in the following way:

{quote}
* You cannot disable the internal directory if your user is an internal user.
* You cannot disable or remove an LDAP or a Crowd directory if your user comes from that directory.
{quote}

Users have found this unintuitive and confusing when they go to edit the directories while being logged in under their directory. A customer suggestion to resolve this confusion has come as the following:

{quote}
I believe you could implement this in a better way. For example - rather than removing the (edit/disable) links, leave the links there but have them display a message informing the user of why they can not edit the directory. The logic to determine this is obviously there, but rather than hide them - just redirect them.
{quote}

This is just a matter of notifying the user in a more effective way.

